  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting the rule of law in the Philippines through enhancing efficiencies and transparency in the judicial process in the family court system.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to support the rule of law through enabling the creation of a process map co-authored with the Supreme court that will help reduce delays and congestion in the Philippine Judiciary, and increase confidence in the justice system. This pilot will focus on the step by step process of two courts: the regular family court and the e-court. It will identify areas for improvement and where the extreme backlogs can be significantly reduced. The process map will be presented at the 2017 Family Court Summit and will help the Supreme Court to assess whether e-courts provide anticipated efficiencies.</narrative>
  </description>
